<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEBATE OVER CAPITAL GAINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Six Democrats Backing Capital Gains Tax" (Part I, July 25): 
</P>
<P>
I do not see this as a partisan issue, nor should it be played as a Bush vs. 
Foley issue. Certainly it is not an "unnecessary giveaway to the rich." 
</P>
<P>
As a retired middle-class professional in my 60s, I would like to sell my house 
(purchased in 1972) and move to a less expensive area. I have not done so 
because of unjust, high capital gains tax. I'm sure there are many, many people 
in my position. 
</P>
<P>
It has been demonstrated that it would generate revenue by encouraging many 
people like myself to sell. 
</P>
<P>
N.M. MYERS 
</P>
<P>
Malibu 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
