</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Look for "Ghostbusters II" to be available in the home video market by 
Christmas. The word Monday from RCA/Columbia at the eighth annual Video 
Software Dealers convention in Las Vegas is that the hit film will hit the 
market in the fourth quarter of this year, possibly by Thanksgiving. The 
expected price tag: around $90. "See No Evil, Hear No Evil" is also headed for 
the video shelves about the same time. Convention delegates now are awaiting 
