<P>
Thunderstorms with lightning but no rain moved toward western and central 
Idaho, where flames have already charred 105,000 acres. The Boise Interagency 
Fire Center, the national fire coordination center, said 23,000 firefighters 
were battling the worst of the fires on 182,000 acres, primarily in Idaho, 
Oregon and California. The center said the war has already cost over $27 
million. More than 220,000 acres have been charred in a bout of mostly 
lightning-caused fires that began July 26. More than 3,000 lightning strikes 
were reported overnight in fire-plagued areas of the West. 
