<P>
HEARING PLEA ON INSURANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With 16 days to go before the Aug. 23 deadline for challenging insurance 
company requests to be exempted from Proposition 103 rate rollbacks, Insurance 
Commissioner Roxani Gillespie was asked by consumer groups to call for 
additional rollback hearings. Although the language of the proposition is 
ambiguous, Gillespie's office and the consumer groups say companies for which 
hearings are not called by the deadline probably will be legally deemed to have 
won their exemptions. So far, Gillespie has called for hearings on only seven 
companies and has tentatively ordered $305 million in rollbacks. Harvey 
Rosenfeld, chairman of the Voter Revolt group, asked Gillespie to call hearings 
for all 445 companies that have applied for exemptions. Gillespie's office said 
more hearings will be called, but it did not say how many. 
</P>
