<P>
BUSH SIGNS $70-BILLION DEBT CEILING INCREASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush signed on Monday a $70-billion increase in the federal debt 
limit, increasing the borrowing ceiling to $2.87 trillion from $2.80 trillion. 
</P>
<P>
The new debt limit will expire on Oct. 31. The debt ceiling is increased once 
or twice a year as the government amasses annual budget deficits. 
</P>
