<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego police Monday were holding a man believed to be responsible for a 
1987 slaying in Miami Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Roland Stewart, 29, phoned police at 8 a.m. Monday and told them he had shot 
and killed Orlando Hawkins on Aug. 11, 1987, said Dave Cohen, a police 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Officers picked up Stewart at the Plaza International Hotel in Mission Valley 
and took him to police headquarters for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
Miami Beach police were expected to arrive in San Diego today to question 
Stewart, Cohen said. San Diego police were unsure of the circumstances of the 
killing, and Miami Beach homicide detectives could not be reached. 
</P>
