VALLEY ROUNDUP: SIERRACIN TO SELL ITS TRANSFLEX DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sierracin Corp. said it agreed to sell its Transflex division to Elmwood 
Sensors for $6 million. Sylmar-based Sierracin, which makes high-tech products 
for the aerospace and manufacturing industries, said it expects to record a 
gain on the sale. The company said the size of the gain has yet to be 
determined but will be reported in results for the third quarter, which ends 
Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
Transflex makes thermal heaters and other industrial products. Elmwood Sensors 
is a unit of FASCO Industries, the U.S. subsidiary of London-based Hawker 
Siddeley. 
