<P>
PANORAMA CITY MAN SHOT FROM CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An apparently gang-related drive-by shooting left an 18-year-old Panorama City 
man in critical condition, Los Angeles police said this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Mario Garcia, 18, was shot about 11:45 p.m. Monday in the back and right arm 
while standing on a curb near his residence in the 14600 block of Blythe 
Street, Detective Ernie Guzman said. No one else was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Police said four men in a car apparently drove past Garcia, then turned around 
at a roadblock installed by the city across Blythe at Willis Avenue to 
discourage drug and gang activities. Police said that as the car passed Garcia, 
a gang slogan was yelled from the car and Garcia was shot. 
</P>
<P>
Garcia was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills where he was in 
critical condition this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Police said that the assailants are believed to be from a gang based outside 
the Blythe Street neighborhood and that it is unclear whether Garcia was a 
rival gang member. 
</P>
