<TEXT>
<P>
A storm during a packed prayer service at a 10,000-seat amphitheater pelted 
participants with hail and cold rain and sent people scrambling for cover. At 
least 130 people were taken to hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
Two of the injured were taken to a coronary intensive care unit, while the rest 
were treated and released Monday night, said Pat Conroy, medical coordinator 
for the five-day Lutheran national youth conference. 
</P>
