<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GOLF GROUP TO SEEK ROLE IN OLYMPICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An international golf association has been formed to seek a place for the sport 
in the Olympics for the first time since 1904, officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
An application was made in February to include golf as a demonstration sport at 
the 1992 Summer Games in Barcelona, Spain, but Olympic rules stipulate a sport 
must have an international governing body. 
</P>
<P>
Because golf has several professional and amateur organizations but none that 
could speak for the entire sport, the World Golf Assn. was created. It has 30 
member nations. 
</P>
<P>
"For more than seven years I have been fighting for the recognition of golf as 
an Olympic sport," WGA President Claude-Roger Cartier of France said. "I hope 
that through the World Golf Association this moment has come." 
</P>
<P>
Golf was contested in the 1900 Olympics in Paris and the 1904 Games in St. 
Louis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
