<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
GERVIN FACES MARIJUANA COUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN ANTONIO, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former San Antonio Spurs basketball star George Gervin was arrested early today 
on charges of driving while intoxicated and possession of marijuana, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Bexar County sheriff's officials said the 37-year-old former NBA All-Star was 
released this morning on a personal recognizance bond. 
</P>
<P>
Although Gervin tested only 0.03% for blood-alcohol content at the San Antonio 
Police Department and the state's definition of intoxication is 0.10%, a 
sheriff's deputy said Gervin failed a visual dexterity field test, according to 
the San Antonio Express-News. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said Gervin was arrested after Deputy Chris Burchell spotted his 
black 1985 Porsche 911S weaving on Interstate 410. 
</P>
<P>
Although Gervin passed the alcohol test, Burchell reported that he refused to 
allow his blood to be tested. 
</P>
<P>
Officials told the newspaper that less than two ounces of marijuana was found 
in the front and rear consoles of the car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Gervin in 1980 
</P>
